{"TopicId":201044,"ForumId":109,"TopicTitle":"What\u0026#039;s up with Rusk and Rask?","CreatedByName":"Kerbal_thrower","CreatedById":210550,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-15T23:41:32Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Kerbal_thrower","CreatedById":210550,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-15T23:41:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nso...can I recreate Anakin vs. Obi-Wan, will things that go between them by ripped apart\u00A0by intense gravity, and will we be able to make lava boats (and colonies)?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-16T00:14:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223940955\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201044\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221615851692\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210550\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kerbal_thrower\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n31 minutes ago, Kerbal_thrower said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nso...can I recreate Anakin vs. Obi-Wan,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSure. Lots of high ground there it looks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n31 minutes ago, Kerbal_thrower said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwill things that go between them by ripped apart\u00A0by intense gravity,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo. Quite the opposite. right in the center is a point where you\u0027d be weightless. Or the game crashes depending on how they program it \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n31 minutes ago, Kerbal_thrower said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nand will we be able to make lava boats (and colonies)?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wouldn\u0027t be surprised if you could make a colony \u0022floating\u0022 on the lava with the support structures hidden underneath. Assuming of course that what we see from space is in fact large bodies of lava oceans.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Drakenred65","CreatedById":154503,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-16T00:25:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin-left:40px;\u0022\u003E\nThere\u2019s a couple of sci fi stories about similar world. Rocheworld aka flight of the Dragonfly is one of them. \u00A0There\u2019s also a Japanese story about a similar situation where someone decided that destabilizing a stable binary planet was the fastest way to strip mine the 2 super earths down to roughly one earth mass each.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-03-16T03:18:21Z\u0022 title=\u002203/16/2021 03:18  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 16, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by \u003Ca href=\u0022/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection\u0022 class=\u0022__cf_email__\u0022 data-cfemail=\u00224f0b3d2e242a213d2a2b797a0f08222e2623612c2022\u0022\u003E[email\u0026#160;protected]\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbal_thrower","CreatedById":210550,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-16T02:54:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223940967\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201044\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221615853676\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Superfluous J\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Superfluous J said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSure. Lots of high ground there it looks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0027t try it Anakin!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jastrone","CreatedById":208489,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-16T08:12:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223941008\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201044\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221615863270\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210550\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kerbal_thrower\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Kerbal_thrower said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0027t try it Anakin!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyou underestimate my power\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223940967\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201044\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221615853676\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Superfluous J\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, Superfluous J said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nright in the center is a point where you\u0027d be weightless\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\non the surface closest to the other planet you would be almost weightless\u00A0 but on the other side there would be very high gravity. this would make airplanes dificult since gravity is not consistant(but i dont think there will be an atmosphere).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nin terms of programing i think they will switch to a different system when it comes to gravity. in ksp1 you will only bee afected by gravity if you are in a sphere of influence of something and then only that planet/moon. in ksp2 the way i think they will do it is\u00A0 by having a line to all planets in a range where things would make a difference and one other for stars wich would just look for the closest star and then measure the distance to them. then do some math and know how much you will be pulled towards that direction. the closest planet would also determine what is down\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-16T08:41:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223941051\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201044\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221615882326\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022208489\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022jastrone\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n25 minutes ago, jastrone said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nin terms of programing i think they will switch to a different system when it comes to gravity.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCorrect. But only in case of these two bodies. Already confirmed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"starcaptain","CreatedById":166799,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-16T19:05:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223941008\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201044\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221615863270\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210550\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kerbal_thrower\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 hours ago, Kerbal_thrower said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0027t try it Anakin!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnikan Kerman\u003Cbr\u003E\nObi Kan Werman\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"PlutoISaPlanet","CreatedById":206057,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-17T15:09:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI do find it some what scary that the devs have not shown rask and rusk again.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-17T16:20:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy? We know what do they look like. We know how they work. We don\u0027t need to see them up close (spoilers!) What more do you expect?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbal_thrower","CreatedById":210550,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-17T16:38:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJeb-Wan vs Billakin\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nBut with aot music instead of duel of the fates because (most of) the sound track is intense music.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}